Edward Heneage (24 July 1802 – 25 June 1880) was a British Whig politician.
Heneage was the son of George Robert Heneage (1768–1833) and his wife Frances Anne Ainslie. He was educated at Eton College.At the 1835 general election he was elected unopposed as a Member of Parliament (MP) for Grimsby, a seat which had been held from 1826 to 1830 by his older brother George. He was re-elected unopposed in 1841 and 1847, but was defeated in a contest in 1852.
